The paper proposes a new memory architecture for navigation in previously unseen environments, which involves a deep network capable of retrieving nodes from a non-parametric graph. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training the deep network using footage of the environment, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
